<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Norway Finalises World Cup Warm-up Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 7 (Xinhua) -- World Cup finalists Norway
will play four pre-finals friendlies, according to reports from
Oslo, Norway.
</P>
<P>
Norway, who have been drawn in Group A with champions Brazil,
Morocco and Scotland, will play France in Marseille on February
28, Belgium in an as yet to be announced venue on March 25,
Denmark on April 22, probably in Copenhagen, and Tunisia on either
May 27 or 28 in Molde, Norway.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegians, who have qualified for their second successive
World Cup finals, have also arranged two training camps for their
players who play abroad to be held in England -- the first to be
held in Blackburn on January 11-12 and another one in February.
</P>
</TEXT>
