<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Egyptian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- The Egyptian Economy Ministry's Firm Committee approved, in
the first week of this month, the establishment of 26 companies
with a total capital of 362 million Egyptian pounds (106.47
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to Ahmad Atta, chairman of the Firm Committee, the
companies include 23 share-holding companies, 13 limited liability
companies and two operating in tourism.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egypt has decided to build 44 new cities on 809,000
hectares and new housing areas on 34,000 hectares, accommodating 8
million people and creating 1.8 million jobs through to 2017 with
a total investment of 79 billion pounds (23.24 billion dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
