<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa Beats Germany in Hopman Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- South Africa beat Germany 2-1
in another round-robin match at the Hopman Cup on Wednesday night
in Perth, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Wayne Ferreira and Amanda Coetzer set the team on its way to
the final, winning through in the deciding mixed doubles in
straight set, 6-2, 6-2, over Tommy Haas and Anke Huber.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Huber, world number 14th, won the opening women
singles against Coetzer 6-3, 6-3 for the unseeded Germany for
their bid of the first win in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
But Ferreira put the South Africa back into the match when he
crashed the teenager Haas, 6-4, 3-6, 6-1, in the following men's
singles.
</P>
<P>
The South Africa pair had no hesitate to bruise the Germans in
the final doubles match though they seldom played togther.
</P>
<P>
South Africa are no one step to the final as they will go for
the second seeded France of Cedric Pioline and Mary Peirce on
Friday, a meeting could assure a berth in the final for them if
they win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
