<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Communist Party Has New Standing Board </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Political Bureau of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) Tuesday
appointed five new members to its Standing Board.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam News Agency said the new members are General Secretary
Le Kha Phieu, Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong, Prime Minister
Phan Van Khai, National Assembly Chairman Nong Duc Manh, and Pham
The Duyet.
</P>
<P>
Duyet, 61, is a permanent member of the Standing Board.
</P>
<P>
Phieu was elected general secretary of the party to replace Do
Muoi at the fourth Plenum of the CPV's Central Committee held in
Hanoi on December 22-29.
</P>
<P>
During the fourth plenum, the Central Committee also elected
four new members to the 19-strong Political Bureau. They are Pham
Thanh Ngan, Nguyen Minh Triet, Phan Dien and Nguyen Phu Trong.
</P>
</TEXT>
