<HEADLINE> UK Wants EU to Play Support Role in Mid-East Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Britain, which is holding the
European Union (EU) presidency, wants the EU to play "the best
supporting actor" in mediating the Middle East peace talks with
Washington as the chief mediator, according to a British
government official.
</P>
<P>
The senior British official was quoted by Reuters as saying
today: "We have to recognize that the United States is the chief
promoter of the Arab-Israeli peace process."
</P>
<P>
"The Americans are re-engaging and Britain is well placed to
influence the Americans," the official said, adding, "We will try
to use the (EU) presidency to build a more effective bridge
between the European Union and the United States in peacemaking."
</P>
<P>
The official pointed out that British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook was determined to use the six-month British presidency to
achieve practical results.
</P>
<P>
During the British presidency, the official said that the Labor
government is likely to propose European monitoring of Palestinian
security cooperation with Israel and settlement activity.
</P>
<P>
"We could contribute by setting objective yardsticks on issues
such as security cooperation, which the Israelis use as a reason
for holding back on withdrawals from Palestinian territory," he
added. 
</P>
