<HEADLINE> Pakistan to Hold Municipal Polls, Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan will hold municipal
elections on April 18 on a non-party basis and conduct a
population and housing census on March 2-18 this year, the cabinet
decided on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was taken at a cabinet meeting chaired by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif, the Associated Press of Pakistan reported.
</P>
<P>
The decision to hold municipal elections in April was made in
the light of recommendations made by the four provincial
governments and the General Council Meeting of the ruling Pakistan
Muslim League on Monday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The elections had been scheduled for February 7, but the
General Council Meeting did not approve the date because of harsh
weather conditions in the month in certain areas of Balochistan
and the North West Frontier Province.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming population and housing census will be the first
one in the country since 1981. A national data base will be
created during the census.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet also discussed a summary submitted by the Ministry
of Water and Power and disapproved any increase in tariff rates.
</P>
