<HEADLINE> Britain Pledges to Create Cleaner, Greener EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Britain pledged here today to
create a cleaner, greener European Union (EU) during its six-month
rotating EU presidency.
</P>
<P>
British Deputy Prime Minister John Prescott told a press
conference this afternoon that environment protection would be a
top priority during Britain's EU presidency which began this
month.
</P>
<P>
"Across Europe, we all want clean air to breathe, clean rivers
and drinking water, healthy sustainable seas around our shores,
alongside continued economic prosperity," Prescott said.
</P>
<P>
Prescott made it clear that his target would be implementing
the agreement on climate change reached at Kyoto, Japan, late last
year. 
</P>
