<HEADLINE> Chirac Urges European Nations to Get Closer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
Wednesday said that European countries will get closer in their
economic policies in 1998, as the European single currency is one
year away from being implemented.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the Paris-based diplomatic corps in the
Elysee presidential palace, Chirac said that the process for
European countries to join the single currency should be
accompanied with an affirmation of the European social model.
</P>
<P>
"As an element for growth and jobs, the single currency will
lead us to a progressive rapprochement of our economic policies.
This process should go hand in hand with the affirmation of the
European social model," he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that a "competitive'' Europe will not contradict
a "humane" Europe, and instead the two features owned by Europe
can be complementary with each other.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said that the euro should be "a happy event" for all
countries in the world, as it would help stabilize international
monetary system.
</P>
<P>
"It will bring a major contribution to a better balance of the
international monetary system. Its birth will be an happy event
for all your countries," he told the ambassadors of all countries
to France. 
</P>
