<DOCNO> XIE19980108.0052 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany Calls for Joint EU-Arab Efforts to Help </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel Wednesday suggested that countries of the European Union
(EU) and the League of Arab States (LAS) make joint efforts to
help stop a recent surge of massacres in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was made by Kinkel in letters to Arab leaders
including LAS General Secretary Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Maguid and
Algerian Foreign Minister Ahmed Attaf, the German foreign ministry
said.
</P>
<P>
It followed another initiative from Kinkel over the weekend
which called for the dispatch of a EU mission to Algeria to offer
help to the government in combating terrorism.
</P>
<P>
In the letters, Kinkel had expressed confidence that the
Algerian government would make all efforts to combat terrorism.
However, he also stressed that the crisis could not be solved by
military means alone and that a political solution was needed, the
German foreign ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Given Algeria's strong resistance to all outside interference,
Kinkel said that the EU respected the country's sovereignty. But
he still held that a joint EU-Arab effort would be helpful.
</P>
</TEXT>
