<HEADLINE> German Machine Orders Up Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to rising foreign demand,
the orders for German machinery products continued to surge in
November, representing a seven percent increase over the level a
year earlier, Germany's machinebuilding association VDMA reported
Wednesday in Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
The VDMA said orders from last September to November registered
a rise of 19 percent on an annual base. During the three months,
foreign orders were up 29 percent while domestic orders up six
percent, compared to the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
In November, overseas orders increased by 12 percent while
domestic orders stagnated partly due to the German government's
delay in reforming economy, according to the organization.
