<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing for Belize Highway Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 16
million U.S. dollar loan to Belize to help upgrade and maintain 64
kilometers of the Southern Highway.
</P>
<P>
The resources will also be used to help rehabilitate about 176
kilometers of rural feeder roads.
</P>
<P>
The preparation work started in 1993. Earlier last year, the
IDB approved a 2.6 million dollar loan to finance technical
assistance for addressing some environmental and social concerns
within the context of a regional development plan to be prepared
with active participation of local residents.
</P>
<P>
The overall objective of the highway project is to improve the
economic opportunities for the people living in the southern
region by integrating that part of the country into the rest of
Belize.
</P>
<P>
Upgrading the road is designed to increase traditional and
nontraditional agricultural activities, promote tourism, improve
access to education, health and other social services as well as
reduce soil erosion and highway maintenance costs. 
</P>
