<HEADLINE> Lebanon Asks UN Peacekeepers to Stay Longer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Lebanon today asked the United
Nations to extend for another six months the mandate of its
Interim Forces in South Lebanon (UNIFIL) which expires on January
31, the official National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The request was contained in a letter addressed to
U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan by Lebanese ambassador to the
U.N. Samir Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
