years, saying that in view of the current Israeli occupation of
south Lebanon and repeated attacks on this area, the UNIFIL
reflects the international community's commitment that Lebanon
must regain its full authority on its territory.
</P>
<P>
The UNIFIL takes the responsibility of helping assure Israeli
withdrawal from south Lebanon and restore peace and security on
both sides of the frontier, the ambassador added.
</P>
<P>
The 4,500-strong peacekeeping force was established in March,
1978 after Israel's invasion of Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel has long complained that the force has been ineffectual
in protecting its northern border from Lebanese guerrillas
attack. 
</P>
