<HEADLINE> First Railway Linking Hungary, Slovenia to Be Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Hungary and Slovenia will soon
jointly build the first railway directly linking the two
neighbors, reports here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The cost of the railway, with a 19.5 kilometers section in
Hungary and a 24 kilometers section in Slovenia, is estimated at
16.7 billion forint (85 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Trains are expected to run at 120-160 kilometers per hour on
this railway line and the travel time between Budapest and
Ljubljana, currently 7 hours, will be shortened by half.
</P>
<P>
Having no railways directly linking the two countries, trains
currently running to either country from the other has to reach
their destinations via Croatia. 
</P>
