<HEADLINE> Chinese National Defense Minister Gives Lecture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese National Defense
Minister General Chi Haotian today reiterated that China should
be always prepared for a people's war, though the world has
developed into a hi-tech age.
</P>
<P>
Chi made the remarks during a lecture at the National Defense
University.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the people's war theory was created during the
Chinese revolutionary wars led by the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
In his lecture, entitled "People's Wars under Hi-Tech
Conditions", the minister said that the theory applies to the new
situation, and is applicable to problems and challenges
accompanying the rapid development of high technology.
</P>
<P>
Development of the nation's hi-tech industry has provided
great impetus to the theory of the people's war, according to Chi.
</P>
<P>
He urged emancipation of the mind, correctly understanding
the trends in worldwide military developments and learning from
foreign armed forces in order to deal with new problems the Chinese
army might meet under the new situation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
