<HEADLINE> HK Basic Law Promotion Committee Holds First Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Basic Law
Promotion Steering Committee held its first meeting Thursday to
discuss the overall stratagem for the promotion of the Basic Law
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
It is the responsibility of every citizen to have a basic and
clear understanding of the contents of the Basic Law of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) of the People's Republic
of China, said Anson Chan, administrative secretary of the SAR and
chairman of the committee.
</P>
<P>
Chan told reporters after the meeting that the Basic Law sets
out very clearly how the principle of "one country, two systems"
operates, what are the systems that will continue to operate
within the SAR and the rights and obligations of each citizen.
</P>
<P>
"The main purpose of the Steering Committee would be to try and
take an overall view and in particular to coordinate the effort of
all the different parties who are currently involved in promoting
the Basic Law," she said.
</P>
<P>
However, the question of promoting the Basic Law is not a new
matter, Chan said.
</P>
<P>
It is an issue that has been dealt with for many years, both
through government efforts and in particular through the sustained
effort of people like members of this committee, through other
voluntary agencies and other organizations, she added.
</P>
<P>
Chan went on to say that the targets of the promotion of the
Basic Law are the community, school students, civil servants and
overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The committee will hold regular meetings in the future to
discuss how to further promote the Basic Law, Chan said.
</P>
<P>
The committee, set up on January 2 with Chan as the chairman
and Ko Siu Wah as vice-chairman, comprises 13 non-governmental and
 nine governmental members.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
