<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Russia led the synchronized
swimming team competition after the first day of technical
preliminaries at the world swimming championships here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian team collected 34.533 points to complete the
technical routine ahead of Japan, which posted 34.230 points.
</P>
<P>
Canada finished third in 34.113 points.
</P>
<P>
The second stage of the team preliminaries - the free routine -
will be held on Saturday. The final scores after the technical
and free routines will decide which of the 17 participating teams
make the final next week.
</P>
