Middle East Peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
Vollebaek made this appeal in Tel Aviv today during his
meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, in which
the two had detailed discussions on the peace process, according
to Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
Vollebaek, who arrived Israel from Jordan on Wednesday to
continue his current Middle East tour, was reportedly said in
Amman before his departure that Norway believes that the Oslo
Accords should be the basis for the peace process.
</P>
<P>
