<HEADLINE> Former Los Angeles Times Business Chief Sentenced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Former editorial business
chief of the Los Angeles Times Charles Boesch was sentenced to
four-year imprisonment Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Boesch, 53, was ordered to pay back 778,000 dollars he stole
from the Los Angeles Times between October 1993 and January 1997
by billing the second largest U.S. newspaper for freelance
articles that were never written.
</P>
<P>
He submitted fake invoices and article summaries to the
accounting department for payment to outside accompanies,
prosecutor Brent Collier said.
</P>
<P>
Boesch was fired as editorial business director last July and
arrested on November 12, after his illegal deeds were uncovered in
audit. 
</P>
