<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), met here today
with Andreas Khol, leader of the Parliamentary Group of the
Austrian People's Party in the National Council of Austria.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, pointed to generally good political and economic
relations since China and Austria forged diplomatic ties in 1971.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from the two countries have maintained a regular
exchange of visits, and bilateral economic cooperation have grown
steadily, according to Wei.
</P>
<P>
