<HEADLINE> Snow Hits Tokyo, Disrupting Traffic Systems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Snow hit Tokyo and its vicinity
Thursday, disrupting traffic systems, forcing train delays and
cancellation of some domestic flights.
</P>
<P>
The snow caused 20 minute delays in arrivals at Tokyo Station
from western and central Japan for Tokaido Shikansen bullet
trains, railway officials said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 12 domestic flights were canceled.
</P>
<P>
An area of low pressure was developing over the south of the
smallest main island of Shikoku, western Japan, and could bring
more heavy snow to Tokyo, the Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
Expecting the snowfall to peak late Thursday night and continue
through early Friday morning, the agency predicted that snowfalls
in the Tokyo metropolitan area would reach up to 20 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
It is the first warning that the agency issued in two years
against heavy snow in the capital area. 
</P>
