<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 85.15 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 8 (Xinhua)-- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Thursday lost 85.15 points to
3,598.16 as against Wednesday's close 3,683.31.
</P>
<P>
The national index dropped by 38.59 points to 1,567.46 from the
previous close of 1,606.05.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the US dollar index were quoted down at 351.86
and 147.75 compared with previous close of 360.33 and 151.61
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities suffered a further sharp setback pushing the sensitive
index down over 85 points on the market on sustained bull
liquidation triggered by the absence of any purchases from foreign
funds in the new year coupled with selling pressure by financial
institutions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
