<HEADLINE> Seniors in Chinese City Going Back to Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Zhao Ruhuan, a 67-year-old
farmer in Jiangmen city, south China's Guangdong Province, is
attending a local training school twice a week to learn how to
grow fruit trees.
</P>
<P>
He said: "This is the first time in my life for me to attend
schools, and I am interested in receiving education." Last year,
he picked 300 kg of fruit from his 20 litchi trees.
</P>
<P>
The school, which is located at Cixi Village, has 300
"students" above the age of 60, or half of the village's old
people.
</P>
<P>
They have a variety of training programs on agricultural
technology, public health, the law and regulations, sports and
local operas.
</P>
<P>
Jiangmen city has collected 50 million yuan to fund 1,430
seniors' associations in its rural areas, which provide regular
education and technology training classes for the elderly.
</P>
