<HEADLINE> German Industrial Orders Slipping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Germany's industrial orders fell
0.8 percent in November after slipping 0.6 percent in both October
and September, the German Economics Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The slump was felt mainly by the exporting industries, which
saw foreign orders dropping 2.9 percent in November from the
October level.
</P>
<P>
Domestic orders, meanwhile, registered a modest 0.9 percent
rise in November.
</P>
<P>
However, when measured against the same month of 1996,
Germany's industrial orders were still much stronger, up 6.2
percent. 
