<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Current Account Deficit Narrows in 3rd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's current account
deficit in the third quarter of last year narrowed significantly
by 66.7 percent, according to official statistics released
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The deficit during the period was down to 1.9 billion ringgit
(413 million U.S. dollars) from 5.7 billion ringgit (1.24 billion
dollars) in the previous quarter, the Statistics Department said
in its Quarterly Balance of Payments Performance for
July-September.
</P>
<P>
The deficit during the third quarter of 1997 also improved as
compared with 2.8 billion ringgit (608 million dollars) recorded
in the corresponding quarter of 1996, it said.  
