<HEADLINE> Output of China's Largest Offshore Oilfield </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China's largest offshore oilfield
at the Yellow River mouth produced 1.5 million tons of crude oil
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The 5-year-old Chengdao oilfield now has 34 platforms with 126
wells. It has produced a total of 3.4 million tons of oil, which was
transported to the shore through a 36-kilometer-long pipeline.
</P>
<P>
Chengdao is affiliated with the Shengli oilfield, China's
second largest, which has produced 630 million tons of
crude oil. 
</P>
