<HEADLINE> Pakhalina Wins Women's 3m Springboard Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian Yulia Pakhalina scored
544.62 points to win the women's 3-meter springboard title at the
world swimming championships here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pakhalina, 20, led all the way to beat Chinese Guo Jingjing
into second place by 25.96 points.
</P>
<P>
The Russian had an impressive season last year, winning the 1m
springboard in the Wellington Grand Prix and 3m springboard in
both the Sydney and Mexico Grand Prix tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Australian Chantelle Michell, who placed 10th after the
semi-finals, clawed back to win the bronze medal with 515.07
points.
</P>
<P>
Reigning World Cup champion Eryn Bulmer of Canada finished a
poor eighth with 485.16 points.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Chinese duo Sun Shuwei and Tian Liang garnered 326.34
points in the men's synchronized platform diving to win China's
first gold medal in the championships.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Michael Kuehne and Jan Hempel took the silver medal
and Russian pair Alexandr Varlamov and Igor Loukashin got the
bronze with 304.02 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
