<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Vice President of Texaco (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng
attended a ceremony today marking the signing of a Sino-Foreign
cooperative contract for coalbed methane production in Huaibei
coal mines.
</P>
<P>
The project between the China United Coalbed Methane Co. Ltd.
(CBM) and U.S.-based Texaco, the first of its kind officially
approved by the state, will involve the exploration of 2,663
square kilometers of coalbed methane resources in east China's
Anhui Province. The project will involve a total investment of 500
million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with senior Texaco Vice-President Robert Black
prior to the signing ceremony, Premier Li Peng said that China has
vast coalbed methane resources, and noted that the planned
exploration and use of related resources will yield substantial
profits.
</P>
<P>
"This will conduce to improving China's energy structure,
accelerating the development of a clean gas energy industry,
reducing air pollution and protecting the environment," according
to Li,
</P>
<P>
The development of coalbed methane in Huaibei coal mines will
have even greater significance since there are a large number of
people living in cities along the Huaihe River, said Li, adding
that related efforts will greatly benefit people living in the
area and enhance the environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that the Chinese and U.S. sides cooperate closely to
ensure that the project enters production at an early date," said
Li.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed the need for strong management, improved
efficiency, exploration and the introduction of new
technology.
</P>
