<HEADLINE> Three Missing, Six Injured in Nevada Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Three people probably died
and six others injured Tuesday as two powerful explosions
rocked a Nevada explosives plant, said reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses reportedly heard two consecutive explosions and saw a
cloud of black smoke over the Sierra Chemical Co. plant, 12 miles
(19 kilometers) east of Reno near the border of California.
</P>
<P>
Local officials were quoted as saying 12 employees were inside
the plant at 8:00 a.m. local time, when the blasts occurred.
</P>
<P>
In the rescue and search work thereafter, six employees were
found injured and sent to the Washoe Medical Center in Reno for
treatment, while three others were missing and thought to be dead.
</P>
<P>
The plant, operational since 1959, produced heavy industrial
chemicals and explosives used in mining and weapons industries.
</P>
