<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Enterprises in China to Use Identification Codes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese foreign trade
enterprises are required as of January 1 to use 13-character
identification codes in their foreign economic and trade business,
according to a notice issued by MOFTEC here today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
(MOFTEC) is responsible for handling issues concerning the codes.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises and those funded by investors from
Taiwan, Hong Kong and Macao will receive their identification
codes when their certificates are renewed.
</P>
<P>
The period from January 1 to April 30 has been established
for certificate renewals.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the enterprises in China will also get their codes
after receiving certificates authorizing them to conduct import
and export business.
</P>
<P>
Those who refuse to apply for the codes will forfeit their
import and export rights.  
</P>
</TEXT>
