<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nuclear Engineering Institute Celebrates 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held here today
to mark the 40th anniversary of the founding of the Beijing
Institute of Nuclear Engineering.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng wrote inscriptions
marking the occasion.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's inscription calls for the institute to follow the
spirit of self-reliance and arduous work. The institute was the
first comprehensive Category A research and design institute in
the nation's nuclear industrial sector. Jiang urged the institute
to make new advances in the realm of nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
Li's inscription encourages the institute to actively develop
nuclear power technology so as to strengthen China's nuclear power
industry.
</P>
<P>
The institute has completed 716 design projects over the past
four decades, including 58 projects which have won awards on
either the national or ministerial levels. Some 469 of 1,054
scientific research projects have also won high-level prizes.
</P>
<P>
The institute, staffed by more than 1,300 experts and
technicians, made eminent contributions to the production of
China's first atomic bomb, first hydrogen bomb, and first
nuclear-powered submarine.
</P>
<P>
The institute is in charge of designing the second-phase
project at the Qinshan Nuclear Power Plant in east China's
Zhejiang Province, the Ling'ao Nuclear Power Plant in south
China's Guangdong Province, and the Lianyungang Nuclear Power
Plant in east China's Jiangsu Province. The second-phase project
at the Qinshan Nuclear Plant will be China's only domestically
designed and built nuclear power plant for commercial use during
the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
