<HEADLINE> Inland Ethnic Area of China Has Rail Outlet to Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China today put into use a
railway line which links Yinchuan, capital of northwest China's
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, with Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The railway line gives Ningxia, a land-locked and
poverty-stricken ethnic area, access to the Chinese coastal areas,
said Yu Gesheng, an official in the regional government.
</P>
<P>
To boost its economic growth and extricate the 700,000 poor
people in the region from poverty, Ningxia must improve its
investment environment, Yu said.
</P>
<P>
An express leaves Yinchuan at 7:40 p.m. every day and
arrives in Guangzhou 62 hours later. There are 68 stops on the
3,021-kilometer line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
