<HEADLINE> Pottery, Porcelain Arts Center Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A pottery and porcelain arts
center opened today in Shanghai, China's largest metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The center contains more than 50,000 outstanding pieces of
pottery and porcelain by hundreds of artisans highlighting the
country's splendid culture of pottery and porcelain-making.
</P>
<P>
The artisans are from Jingdezhen City in Jiangxi Province and
Yixing City in Jiangsu Province. Jingdezhen is called China's
"porcelain capital" and Yixing is known as the "pottery capital."
</P>
<P>
In addition to exhibiting these works, the center includes a
workshop where domestic and foreign artists can exchange their
experience.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the center said that the Dekang Auction Company in
Shanghai will conduct auctions on precious pottery and porcelain
works each month.
</P>
<P>
Pottery and porcelain fans can also attend regular training
classes at the center on the procedures of making pottery and
porcelain.  
</P>
