<HEADLINE> Shanghai Prepares for Upcoming Peak Travel Period </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Municipality has
prepared well for the upcoming peak travel during the Spring
Festival holiday season.
</P>
<P>
From Jan. 8 to Feb. 26, the municipal transport departments in
this largest city of China are expected to handle 7.8 million
travellers, up 1 percent from last year.
</P>
<P>
To facilitate the holiday passenger flow, the municipality will
add 28 passenger ships and more aircraft.
</P>
<P>
The railway department, for example, plans to put into use
101.5 pairs of trains to carry an estimated 4.16 million
travellers.
</P>
<P>
While increasing the number of trains, aircraft and ships,
transport departments will also try to improve their services. The
railway department will raise the speed of trains and increase the
convenience of booking tickets.
</P>
<P>
The transportation of non-local laborers remains the key
problem, according to local government officials.
</P>
<P>
Half of the 2.37 million non-local laborers working in the city
will be leaving for home during the peak period.
</P>
<P>
The Spring Festival, or Chinese lunar new year, is the most
important traditional holiday in the country. During a nearly
two-month period, large numbers of college students and non-local
workers will head home for family reunions.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
