<DOCNO> XIE19980108.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cholera Situation Stablized in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The cholera outbreak in Uganda
has been brought under control, Health Minister Crispus Kiyonga
said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony where a Danish agreement supporting
his ministry was signed, Kiyonga revealed that up to January 4,
new cholera cases in the Ugandan capital Kampala has dropped from
200 a day at its peak to 100-150 at present.
</P>
<P>
The epidemic has claimed so far 300 lives and infected 4,000
people in Uganda, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
Of all the cases, 2,723 were recorded in Kampala with 74
deaths. Mbale, the heavily hit district in the east, witnessed
560 patients with 47 deaths.
</P>
<P>
Bugiri, also in the east, reported 59 cases between December
29 and January 5. The situation there is said to be under
control.
</P>
<P>
Eleven districts in the north have not received a single case
of the disease this season, according to Sam Okware, Chairman of
the National Cholera Task Force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
