<HEADLINE> Coalition Era Has Come to Stay in India: Gujral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 8 (Xinhua)-- Indian Prime Minister Inder
Kumar Gujral said Thursday that the coalition era had come to stay
in India.
</P>
<P>
"We are evolving from a single party rule to multi-party rule
and as an observer away from the seat I occupy, multi-party rule
is inevitable," Gujral said.
</P>
<P>
"Any government that will come to power after the elections
will be a coalition government," he said shortly after his
inaugural address at the fourth global partnership summit
organized by the Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) in
Chennai, capital of Tamil Nadu in southern India.
</P>
<P>
All the three or four major combinations that were in the race
for power in the polls were basically coalitions. The forthcoming
polls to be held from February 16 this year would see installation
of yet another coalition government at the center, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
