<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Shares Fall by 2.98 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices shed
almost three percent Thursday amid fear of rising interest rates
as Southeast Asian currencies plunged to new record lows.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index, which traces the performance of 33 blue
chips listed on the Hong Kong bourse, fell 284.08 points, or 2.98
percent Thursday to close at 9,254.53.
</P>
<P>
The losses came after the key index tumbled nearly 600 points,
or six percent Wednesday to dive below the 10,000-point benchmark
level. The sharp plunge was triggered by the continuing steep fall
of regional currencies, according to brokers.
</P>
<P>
Property shares were the hardest hit, which plummeted 612
points, or 4.85 percent Thursday. Other sub-indices for finance,
utilities, commerce and industry also dropped.
</P>
<P>
H shares (China state-owned enterprises listed on the Stock
Exchange of Hong Kong), and red chips (China-affiliated
corporations), both fell by more than eight percent.
</P>
<P>
Turnover stood at 12.528 billion HK dollars (1.6 billion US
dollars).  
</P>
