<HEADLINE> Joint Study on Realignment of Waters Near Macao to Be Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Macao and the Pearl River Water
Resources Committee (PRWRC) of China will do a joint study on
the realignment of the waters near Macao.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Macao Harbor Bureau and of the PRWRC
under the Ministry of Water Resources signed an agreement here on
Wednesday on the realignment plan. The two sides will each make
their own efforts to complete a report to be submitted early next
year.
</P>
<P>
The joint study aims to work out ways to ensure a smooth
release of floodwater at the estuary of the Pearl River, to expand
shipping, to protect water resources and to make reasonable use of
shoals, said the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The area for the planned dredge will cover more than 200 square
kilometers around Macao, with the realignment of three waterways
as the key task.
</P>
<P>
The project will cost about 15.1 million yuan (about 1.82
million US dollars), of which each side will share half. After all
study is completed, a report on the planned realignment will be
submitted in early 1999.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several years, reckless reclamation projects
alongside the waterways near Macao have produced a negative effect
on the water flow, the release of floodwater and the water
environment, experts said, adding that a scientific and reasonable
development of the area is urgently needed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
