<HEADLINE> Mozambique Records $335M Domestic Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique recorded direct
domestic investment worth of 335 million U.S. Dollars between
1985 and September 1997, a media report said here today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a source at the Investment Promotion Center
as saying that a total of 757 investment projects were approved
in the period.
</P>
<P>
Of the projects, 218 are in the industry sector, involving a
total investment of 143 million Dollars. The agriculture sector
attracted 62 million Dollars from investors for 134 projects.
</P>
<P>
The tourism and hotel sector registered 76 projects, with an
investment of 33 million Dollars. The construction sector
reported 42 projects with investment totaling 30 million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, direct investment in Mozambique saw a
sharp rise in 1992 after the end of the 16-year-old civil war.
</P>
<P>
In that year, authorities approved 55 million Dollars in
investment, compared to an average of 4.5 million Dollars during
the war period from 1985 to 1991.
</P>
<P>
Domestic investment declined drasticly to 7.55 million Dollars
in 1993. Hereafter, it managed to maintain an average of 49
million Dollars a year, the source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
