Israeli bombardment since the start of this year. The previous
one was wounded in the same area three days ago.
</P>
<P>
Six hours later, Iranian-backed Hezbullah, or Party of God,
donated a roadside bomb against a patrol of South Lebanese Army
(SLA), Israeli militia ally, when they were travelling on a road
inside the occupation zone, according to a statement released by
Hezbullah.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that the explosion had inflicted direct
casualties on the SLA soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The tit-for-tat conflict between Israeli troops and Lebanese
guerrillas has lasted for more than 10 years since Israel carved
out a 1,200-square-kilometer area in south Lebanon as a security
zone to protect its north from guerillars attack. 
</P>
