<HEADLINE> PC Owners' Ideas Changing In Northeast China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Personal computer owners in
the northeast China city of Changchun have began to adopt a new
attitude toward the computer as their numbers grow, according to a
recent survey by the "Changchun Evening News".
</P>
<P>
The city's residents now have a better understanding of the
personal computer and more people are coming to regard the machine
as an helper in their daily lives instead of a toy.
</P>
<P>
Of 1,710 people questioned by letter and fax, college students
showed the most enthusiasm for the computer and accounted for 29.3
percent of the replies. Other responses came from the field of
medicine, education, and the military.
</P>
<P>
The survey found that nearly half those responding wanted a
brand-name computer like Legend, IBM, or Compaq, the clear
favorites of the people of Changchun.
</P>
<P>
As for price, about 40 percent of those responding said that
they prefer computers that cost from 7,000 to 10,000 yuan. At the
same time, people are looking for greater speed, a wider range of
functions, and greater workability in their computer.
</P>
<P>
The Internet was the most favorite item in the survey for about
three-fourths of those responding, and half the people were keen
to know more about Windows 95 software.  
</P>
</TEXT>
