<HEADLINE> Economic Reforms Enjoy Consensus in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Inder Kumar
Gujral said Thursday that the economic reforms process has won the
support of major political parties in the country.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the fourth global partnership summit organized by
the Confederation of Indian Industry in Chennai, capital of Tamil
Nadu, southern India, Gujral said, "Let me assure you that the
reform process enjoys a good measure of consensus and major
political parties have made it part of their economic agenda."
</P>
<P>
