this score as also on the overall issue of opening up of the
economy, particularly in the wake of severe economic and financial
crisis enveloping some of the East and Southeast Asian countries.
We need to draw lessons from what has happened while charting out
our course for the future," he further said.
</P>
<P>
At a recent Planning Commission meeting, he pointed out, it was
felt that the country needs to double its investments in
infrastructure areas in the next five years from what was done in
the last 50 years.  
