<HEADLINE> Macao Publishes Comprehensive Atlas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A comprehensive atlas of Macao has
been published here for the first time and is now available in
bookstores in Hong Kong and Macao.
</P>
<P>
Published by the Macao Foundation, the atlas is composed of
maps, forms and explanations in Chinese, English and Portuguese
languages. It is said to be best for academic study, students and
teachers as well as tourists.
</P>
<P>
The maps and forms show the details of Macao's geographical
location, geological structure, waters, landscape, change of
coastlines, climate, population distribution, residential areas,
land use and reclamation from sea.
</P>
<P>
It also shows the details of industrial distribution, the ups
and downs of foreign trade, hotels and scenic sites, schools and
cultural facilities. The atlas also includes a detailed map of
Macao streets.
</P>
<P>
It gives users an introduction of Macao's history, location and
transportation, among other things.
</P>
<P>
The atlas is so far the most comprehensive one published in
Macao. Due to excessive reclamation from sea, the latest map,
which was published in 1993, has been described as outdated.
</P>
<P>
Macao including its two islands now has a land mass of about 23
square kilometers and a population of 425,000 in mid-1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
