<HEADLINE> Northern Chinese Province Developing Pillar Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province will take chemicals, building materials, metallurgy,
machine building and foodstuff as its pillar industries in the
economic plan for the 1995-2010 period.
</P>
<P>
This is a revised plan after the province found its pillar
industries previously set by the provincial government were
similar with that of Beijing and Tianjin, said Miao Ziyi, head of
long-term planning division under the provincial planning
commission.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, the proportion of the added-value of the five pillar
industries in Hebei's gross domestic product (GDP) will be
increased from one quarter to more than one third, Miao said.
</P>
<P>
To avoid overlapping with other regions, Hebei will lay the
emphasis on sensitive materials, medical intermediate and refined
chemicals, high grade cement, new materials, deep-processed
metals, light-duty automobiles and spare parts, power transmission
equipment, environmental facilities and food packing machinery,
and protein drinks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
