<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Chinese Textile Industry Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANHUI, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The textile industry of China's
Anhui Province has improved somewhat in 1997 year and is expected
to reduce losses by about 130 million yuan from the more than 400
million yuan of last year.
</P>
<P>
During the January-November period, the sector's losses were
down 84.69 million yuan, or 22 percent, from the same period of
last year, according to the provincial textile council.
</P>
<P>
The improved efficiency was achieved by reducing the number of
spindles and redundant workers, increasing research, and
supporting the garment industry.
</P>
<P>
The province has gotten rid of 100,000 spindles this year and
laid off 63,000 workers. It plans to eliminate 280,000 spindles
and further cut its work force by 25,000 people next year, and the
sector expects to be showing a profit within three years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
