<HEADLINE> Pakhalina Leads after Women's 3m Springboard Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Russian Yulia Pakhalina will go into
the women's 3-meter springboard final with a big lead over the
rest of field at the world swimming championships here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pakhalina, World Cup silver medalist in the 3m springboad,
garnered 522.39 points after the semi-finals early afternoon,
beating Chinese Guo Jingjing into second place in 506.01.
</P>
<P>
Russian Vera Ilyina collected 499.74 points to come in third.
</P>
<P>
Pakhalina had an impressive season last year, winning the 1-meter
springboard in the Wellington Grand Prix and 3m springboard in
both the Sydney and Mexico Grand Prix tournaments.
</P>
<P>
Reigning World Cup champion Eryn Bulmer of Canada placed fifth in
498.36. 
