<HEADLINE> Clinton to Visit Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton will
visit Angola in the first half of this year, foreign ministry
spokesman Anercio Cadete has said.
</P>
<P>
Cadete was quoted by the official News Agency of Angola as
saying Wednesday that Clinton's visit to Angola is part of his
planned African tour, which will take him to the Democratic
Republic of Congo, Congo Brazzaville, South Africa, Zimbabwe,
Ethiopia, Rwanda, Uganda and Egypt.
</P>
<P>
last December, U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright had
visited most of the above-mentioned countries.
</P>
<P>
Clinton's visit is expected to be preceded by a tour of these
nations by U.S. Vice-President Al Gore in the first quarter of
this year, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He noted Clinton's visit depends on the stability in southern
Africa and is aimed at consolidating and strengthening the U.S.
relations with Angola and other countries in the sub-region.
