<HEADLINE> China to Expand Textile Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 8 (Xinhua) -- China plans to expand its export
of textiles in 1998, according to today's International Business
Daily.
</P>
<P>
The paper says that a joint working conference held by the
State Economic and Trade Commission and China National Textile
Council decided that China would raise textile export tax rebate
from 9 percent to 11 percent, and promised to give 15 percent of
its quota of textile export to the United States to those
businesses that have export rights.
</P>
<P>
The nation will also provide credits for cotton spinning
machines and encourage their exports.
</P>
<P>
According to the meeting, China exported 46 billion US dollars
worth of textiles last year. That of garments surpassed 32 billion
US dollars.  
