<HEADLINE> Manila Shares Drop Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine stock market
dropped by 5.24 percent Thursday on fear of a weaker Asian
currency market and the uncertainty of the country's economic
future.
</P>
<P>
The 30-share Philippine Stock Exchange composite index (Phisix)
plunged 91.49 points to 1,655.85 points while the broader
all-shares index fell 26.36 points to close at 504.36.
</P>
<P>
Worries of further increase in interest rates and higher
inflation in the first quarter of 1998 also put pressure on the
stock market.
</P>
<P>
Total value turnover was at 1.43 billion on a meager volume of
678.45 million shares, the lowest in almost five years.
</P>
<P>
The continuing negative investors' sentiment on a volatile
currency market has pushed down the Phisix for the third
consecutive days. The Phisix shed 52.24 points on Tuesday and
73.26 points on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the chaos in the stock market will not ease as
Asian currencies continue to reel under speculative attacks.
</P>
<P>
Among the main losers Thursday are Philippine Long Distance
Telephone Co., Manila Electric Co, and Metropolitan Bank &AMP; Trust
Co. 
</P>
