expensive following the depreciation of the ringgit against the
greenback.
</P>
<P>
"The problem is compounded by the fact that not only imports
from the United States and Europe are denominated in U.S. dollars,
but also those from other countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. dollar has been appreciating steeply against
Malaysia's currency -- the ringgit. The ringgit which touched an
intra-day low of 4.8800 to the greenback Wednesday kicked off
Thursday at 4.5800/61 to the U.S. dollar.  
