<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Fishing Firm Gutted by Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, January 8 (Xinhua) -- A fish processing and
exporting company in Dar es Salaam has been gutted by a fire,
suffering a loss of more than 40 million shillings (about 80,000
U.S. Dollars), press reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Two containers of fish processing equipment and instrument for
three boats owned by "Fruit de la Mer" Ltd, each worth 20 million
shillings, were burnt to ashes after the fire broke out at around
11 a.m. Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Losses of other properties are not immediately known, said the
company's sales manager, Salim Issak.
</P>
<P>
The fire may disrupt the business of the company, which has
operated for two years at Chang'ombe in the city.
</P>
<P>
Employees and the city's fire brigade have devoted all efforts
battling the tongues of flames, but were frustrated by poor
equipment and lack of water and foam, the company's engineers
said.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the Environmental Committee of Poverty Africa,
Lieutenant Colonel, Juma Mnyube, blamed the firemen and called on
the government to equip them with adequate facilities.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is suspected to be an electric fault,
engineers with the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
