<HEADLINE> Chinese Experts to Help Hybrid Rice Growth in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Two Chinese rice experts have
left for Bangladesh to help the neighboring agricultural country
to draft a national plan for spreading hybrid rice technology.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Kunlu and Wu Xiaojin, two experts on hybrid rice research
from Hunan-based China national hybrid rice engineering research
center, is to make appraisal of installations of the hybrid rice
research institutions and breeding capacity of hybrid rice seeds
before helping make a medium-range development plan of hybrid rice
for the country.
</P>
<P>
During their four-month stay in Bangladesh, Zhou and Wu is to
make trial growth of high-yield Chinese hybrid rice and teach
local agro-technicians techniques of breeding seeds and
cultivating hybrid rice.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is a country with a big population but a small
amount of per capita land. The rice output accounts for 95 percent
of the country's grain output. The hybrid rice technology is
expected to help the country to raise the rice production
capacity.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization has funded a
medium-term development plan of Bangladesh's research and seed
breeding of the hybrid rice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
