<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Calls for Joint Efforts to Promote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Lieutenant-General
Khin Nyunt urged residents in border areas to work with the
government to promote economic development.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the Myanmar State Peace and
Development Council, made the call at an opening ceremony for a
bridge on the Kengtung-Mongla road in eastern Shan state of
Myanmar, the official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Khin Nyunt, who is also chairman of the Work Committee for the
Development of Border Areas and National Races, said border areas
development projects have been implemented with added momentum in
recent years to improve living conditions of the national races in
the areas.
</P>
<P>
The newly-opened bridge shortens the distance between Kengtung
and Mongla, and the 99.2-kilometer Kengtung-Mongla road will also
link Mongla to the Myanmar-China border and Tachilek to the
Myanmar-Thailand border, becoming a direct transport link to China
and Thailand and also to Laos via Mongla area.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Commander of the Triangle Region Major-General
Thein Sein as saying that the links with neighboring countries
will lead to better trade and commerce with them and bring about
progress in the region.  
