<HEADLINE> Slovakia Lowers Import Tariff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Slovak government has decided
to lower the country's import tariff from seven percent to five
percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia made the decision to meet the demands of international
trade, and to prepare for joining the Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development, a report in the newspaper Hospodarske
Noviny (Economic News) said.
</P>
<P>
The decision was welcomed by the European Union and three other
member countries of the Central Europe Free Trade Zone, Hungary,
Poland and the Czech Republic.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia raised the import tariff to seven percent last July to
balance its foreign trade deficit. This met strong opposition from
the country's trade partners, especially the Czech Republic.
</P>
</TEXT>
