<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Gets New Automobile Alarm System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 8 (Xinhua) -- The "VPW", an automobile alarm
system that can help police locate stolen automobiles in less than
20 seconds, is now available in Tianjin, a north China port city.
</P>
<P>
The alarm system was invented by the Zhengdawang
Telecommunications Co. Ltd. and the Zhongyou Company, using new
DSP processing and magnified frequency telecommunications
technology.
</P>
<P>
According to company executives, a lost or stolen car can be
found in less than 20 seconds after the driver reports the number
of the car to a monitoring center.
</P>
<P>
The system can also be used to locate the position of a moving
object and to follow it in a certain area, or to follow the
positions of ships in a harbor, within a 15-m. range of error.
</P>
<P>
The system is suitable for banks, department stores,
warehouses, or even individual households for emergency purposes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
