<HEADLINE> Liaoning Accelerates Technological Upgrading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning, a leading heavy
industrial center in northeast China, will speed up the process of
technological transformation in the next three years.
</P>
<P>
It will give priority to the upgrading of 50 key projects
including production of auto engines and radical tires.
</P>
<P>
Preparations are being made to upgrade a polyethylene project
which has an annual production capacity of 360,000 tons and a PVC
project with a capacity of 200,000 tons annually.
</P>
<P>
The province will encourage 100 large and medium-sized
enterprises to build Sino-foreign joint ventures and carry out
technological cooperation with the top 500 firms in the world.
</P>
<P>
The move will help Liaoning achieve its goal of cutting the
losses incurred by state-owned industrial enterprises by 14
percent while raising the ratio of state assets of well-performed
enterprises to 74 percent in three years.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has 926 medium and large state-owned enterprises, or
about 10 percent of the national total. 
</P>
