<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hungarian Foreign Policy Will Not Change </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Budapest, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian President Goncz Arpad
said Wednesday that foreign policy will not change regardless of
the outcome of the general election scheduled for May.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with newly-appointed foreign ambassadors, Goncz
said 1997 was a successful year diplomatically.
</P>
<P>
Hungary made a breakthrough in the integration process with
Europe and made a marked improvement in relations with neighboring
countries, said the president.
</P>
<P>
The economy is also improving following several years of
effort, he added. 
</P>
