<HEADLINE> Colombia Decides Foreign Commerce Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTA FE DE BOGOTA, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian
government has defined its policy for foreign commerce in 1998,
the Ministry of Foreign Commerce said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Colombia expects to modernize its means for fostering foreign
trade, and to strengthen foreign trade especially in medium and
small-sized businesses.
</P>
<P>
Regional integration was another way to strengthen exports,
and to allow the free transportation of cargo through Andean
countries.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the Congress was discussing and was likely to
pass a project that would pave the way for signing foreign
investment accords.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian government also expected to improve its trade
relations with the United States and Central American countries,
and to reach an agreement with Canada, one of the most promising
markets for Colombia, the ministry said. 
