<HEADLINE> Small State-Owned Enterprises in Hebei Undergoing Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 8 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,780 small
state-owned enterprises in north China's Hebei Province have
introduced various reform measures.
</P>
<P>
Some 6,520 firms, 60 percent of the province's total, have
reorganized their state assets to make sure they are being fully
utilized, said a provincial official from the commission of
economic restructuring.
</P>
<P>
Under a more flexible policy to be adopted by the provincial
government, small state-owned enterprises in the next two years
will be auctioned, reorganized, merged or form stock partnerships
with others.
</P>
<P>
Workers in 3,859 small state-owned enterprises have become
shareholders. Meanwhile, 1,718 joint stock cooperatives have been
established.
</P>
<P>
As a result, asset liabilities of small state-owned enterprises
in Hebei dropped from 83 percent at the beginning of 1997 to 75
percent in October. Losses incurred by these enterprises were
reduced by 25 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
