<HEADLINE> Ferrari to Seek '98 Title with New F-300 Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ferrari team today unveiled its
new F-300 car with which it hopes drivers Michael Schumacher and
Eddie Irvine to capture the 1998 Formula One championship.
</P>
<P>
The F in the new name stands for Ferrari while the 300 refers
to the number of cubic centimeters (cc) of each of its ten
cylinders.
</P>
<P>
The F-300 was presented in a ceremony held at Maranello,
Ferrari's high-tech wind tunnel, designed by Italian architect
Renzo Piano, with the participation of the two drivers together
with Ferrari Chairman Luca Cordero di Montezemolo, team manager
Jean Todi and test driver Luca Baduer.
</P>
<P>
"We want to win the 1998 championship, if we do not it will
mean that we have missed our primary objective for the season",
the Ferrari chairman told the press.
</P>
<P>
The new car is made out of carbon fibers, it is 4.34 meters
long, 1.795 meters wide, 961 centimeters high and weights some 600
kg. It has a new independent suspension system in both front and
back as well as a new semi-automatic transmission and electronic
gear shift control for seven forward gears and one reverse gear.
</P>
<P>
The car is powered by Ferrari's 047 V 10-cylinder engine, with
a total displacement of 2997cc, while the exact number of
horsepower, traditionally `top secret', is said to be above
700. The electronic injection and ignition are made by Magneti
Marelli.
</P>
<P>
The car's red and white coloring are the same as last
season. Compared to last year's model, this year's car has a
higher nose and smaller rear where the wheel have more freedom of
movement in relation to the spoiler. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
