<HEADLINE> Jordan Leads All-Star Voting for East Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Michael Jordan and Grant Hill
are listed on the top in receiving votes in Eastern Conference
balloting so far for the 1998 All-Star Game, the NBA said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chicago Bulls star Jordan, who last week overtook Hall of Famer
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar for consecutive games with at least 10 points
(790), has gained 249,077 votes at guard.
</P>
<P>
Jordan has been the leading vote-getter eight times since 1987.
Injured Orlando Magic guard Penny Hardaway is second with 149,583
votes.
</P>
<P>
Hill of the Detroit Pistons leads forwards with 247,526 votes
while Shawn Kemp of the Cleveland Cavaliers is second with
111,840. Glen Rice of Charlotte was placed in the third position
with 73,733 votes.
</P>
<P>
Atlanta Hawks center Dikembe Mutombo, a two-time NBA Defensive
Player of the Year, led in the voting for centers with 147,614.
Patrick Ewing of the New York Knicks, who was out for the season
after hurting his wrist, has won 134,836 votes.
</P>
<P>
The All-Star Game is scheduled for February 8 at New York's
Madison Square Garden. Starters will be announced January 25.
</P>
