<HEADLINE> IADB Grants Record Loans To Latin American Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IADB) has disbursed 5.43 billion dollars in
credits for Latin America over 1997, said today a report of the
institution.
</P>
<P>
The IADB, an international institution that turns out 43
percent of its portfolio to social-related programs, was the main
source of credit for Latin American countries for the fourth year
in a row.
</P>
<P>
The bank said that it disbursed 4.31 billion dollars to the
region during 1996 while the total approved for 1997 was 6.31
billion dollars, of which 5.43 billion have already gone to
specific projects.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, IADB funds supported 99 initiatives of credit for
infrastructure projects managed by the private sector without
governmental intervention.
</P>
<P>
The international institution also financed 294 projects of
technical cooperation to a total of 73.6 million dollars.
</P>
