<HEADLINE> Professional Schools In Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Professional schools in
central China's Hunan Province have been doing well, since the
local government and various departments have worked hard to
encourage education in the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up 766 professional schools at various
levels, which can train 227,500 people per year. They have 562,700
young people studying in them, accounting for 56.34 percent of
senior high-school students, according to one official. There are
130 provincial or national key professional schools in Hunan that
were approved by the State Education Commission.
</P>
<P>
The schools cover a 13.24-sq km campus, and have 194 million
yuan worth of educational equipment and 67 million yuan worth of
instruments for fieldwork.
</P>
<P>
The province has also improved teaching and administration. All
graduates have to pass examinations and most of them have earned a
number of certificates that attest to their technical skill. They
play an important role in a wide range of work with machinery,
railways, the chemical industry, transportation,
telecommunications, finance, and business and trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
