<HEADLINE> Five Missing, Six Injured in US Plant Explosions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Five people were missing and
six others injured in two powerful blasts that leveled an
explosives plant near Reno, Nevada, today, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen people were inside the Sierra Chemical Co. plant near
Lockwood, about 19 kilometers east of Reno, when the blasts
happened, the Associated Press said in a report.
</P>
<P>
Both main buildings at the plant were flattened, windows of
smaller buildings at the plant were shattered and the buildings
were riddled with shrapnel. The blasts were felt as far as 30
kilometers away.
</P>
<P>
The plant owner said the buildings contained cast primer, a
TNT-based product used in mining.
</P>
<P>
Four of the injured remained at the hospital, three in
satisfactory condition with burns. 
</P>
