<HEADLINE> UN to Send Technical Survey Team to Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations is
going to send a technical team to Sierra Leone as early as Friday,
UN spokesman Juan Carlos Brandit announced today.
</P>
<P>
Carlos said the purpose of the mission is to assess the
conditions on the ground and to formulate recommendations to the
UN Secretary-General concerning the role of UN in the
implementation of the peace accord in Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Secretary-General will incorporate their
recommendations in his second sixty-day report on Sierra Leone,
which he is scheduled to submit to the Security Council of the
United Nations by February 8.
</P>
<P>
A military Junta came to power on May 25, 1996 in Sierra Leone.
The move has been condemned by the international community, which
urges the junta to step down and restore the power of the
democratically elected government as soon as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
