<HEADLINE> Algeria Rejects Foreign Role in Internal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- Algerian government spokesman
Habib Chawki Hamraoui today reiterated that Algeria categorically
rejects any attempt to interfere in its internal affairs from any
quarter.
</P>
<P>
Hamraoui, also minister of communication, culture, was quoted
today by the Algerian news agency as saying that any attempt under
any cover to create doubts about the sources of terrorism is
totally condemned by Algeria.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to the statements made in certain Western
capitals regarding the terrorist crimes being committed in
Algeria. The Algerian government deeply regrets the circulation of
such confusion and misconception, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hamraoui strongly condemned the indiscriminate acts of
terrorism against the Algerian people, particularly since the
beginning of the current fasting month of Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
A number of Western countries have been exerting pressure on
Algeria to accept investigation into the nature of the terrorists,
and have called upon the Algerian government to safeguard the
legitimate rights of the Algerian people against terrorist actions.
</P>
<P>
Algeria is currently experiencing relative tension on account
of the mounting acts of terrorism throughout the country,
especially since the beginning of Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday night three massacres took place in an area about
300 kilometers southwest of the capital city of Algiers, in which
at least 62 people were killed and 38 others wounded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
