<HEADLINE> General Assembly to Put UNDP in Charge of Disaster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 7 (Xinhua) -- The UN General Assembly
adopted a resolution to transfer responsibility for natural
disaster mitigation, prevention and preparedness from the UN
Department of Humanitarian Affairs to the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), a release from UNDP said today.
</P>
<P>
In response to the resolution, UNDP is establishing a Disaster
Management Program (DMP) starting this month within its
Emergency Response Division, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The release said the new program will focus primarily on
natural disasters, and the DMP's main goals are: to strengthen the
capacities of governments and non-governmental organizations; to
prepare for and manage for risks and vulnerabilities to disasters;
to help integrate disaster management into national development
planning; and to strengthen UN disaster Management Teams and their
national counterparts in disaster prone countries.
</P>
<P>
A priority for DMP is to confront disasters related to EL NINO,
and the United Nations has approved a grant of 2.3 million U.S.
dollars to enable UNDP to carry out its new tasks, the release
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
